// Enrollment service contract. Boundary source of truth.
//
// The service trust domain's bootstrap door: a joining node presents a
// pre-shared bootstrap secret and a certificate-signing request, and the
// cluster trust anchor returns a short-lived signed identity plus the root to
// trust. This is the one path consulted at enrollment (and rotation); steady
// state peer-to-peer auth is direct mTLS against the returned root and never
// touches this service. It is kept logically separate from the placement
// directory so "the root of all trust" and "where everything is" are not one
// compromise surface.

